The Assembly Commission, which is now preparing legislation for the introduction of name changes, said: "The final decision on what members of the Welsh Assembly will, of course, be on the members themselves."
The 2017 Welsh Government Act gave the Welsh Assembly the power to change its name.
In June, the commission published the results of a public meeting on proposals, where broad support was given to the variant of calling the Assembly the Welsh Parliament.
In terms of the title of members of the Assembly, the commission preferred the name Welsh Parliament Member, or WMP, but the MWP variant received the largest support in public discussion.
